<TITLE> Ashura teaches resolution against repression: Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com)  On the eve of Ashura, prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Wednesday said the historic event teaches humanity to stand up against brutality and repressions. "A unique day in Muslim world, Ashura teaches us resolution against repression and brutality. The spirit of the day guides us not give in to injustice and stand firm against violence and hatred," she said. In a message, she said prophet Muhammad's grand son Imam Hossain was brutally murdered in Karbala on the day. "This is a heart-rending incident in the history of the humanity," she said. She urged all to harness the spirit of the Ashura in society. Like every year, this year too will mark the day with a pompous rally carrying two symbolical tombs Imam Hossain and brother Imam Hasan, and Tajia procession starting from Hossaini Dalan in the city. bd
